-- 3M sees 2008 sales, earnings up by double digits
-- 
-- Wed Dec 12, 2007 8:24am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/12/us-3m-outlook-idUSWEN291520071212

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - 3M Co ( MMM.N ), the maker of such products as Scotch tape and optical films for liquid crystal displays, said on Wednesday it expects double-digit sales and earnings growth in 2008, and estimated 2008 earnings per share in a range of $5.44 to $5.47. 

 Analysts polled by Reuters Estimates were expecting 3M to earn $5.42 per share next year. The diversified manufacturer, which also makes Post-It notes and Thinsulate insulation, provided the forecast in presentation materials ahead of its analyst meeting later on Wednesday. (Reporting by Nick Zieminski, editing by Gerald E. McCormick)